def: To cause to loathe, or feel disgust at. [Scot. & Prov. Eng.]
Divination by inspecting a burning coal.
Resembling the tail of a squirrel; -- generally said ofbranches which are close and dense, or of spikes of grass likebarley.

A crimson or pink color; also, a style of dress cut low andsquare in the neck; also, a mode of dressing the hair by drawing itstraight back from the forehead over a roll; -- so called after theMarchioness de Pompadour of France. Also much used adjectively.
Serving or tending to reconcile. Bp. Hall.
The act of traducing; misrepresentation; ill-founded censure;defamation; calumny. [R.] Shak.
An ethereal or spiritlike state. J. H. Stirling.
Below the temple; below the temporal bone.
